node.text:
This year's #Sandhurst Tom Surdyke Leadership Award winner goes to Cadet Ethan Erickson with The College of Saint Benedict Saint John's University @fightingsaintsbattalion.

The award is named in memory of Cadet Thomas Surdyke who died from injuries sustained while saving the life of a drowning stranger. Surdyke was a member of the Company B4 @b4_buffaloes Sandhurst team his Plebe year.

Congratulations to USMA Black who won the overall competition. The top teams are: 

1. USMA Black @usma_sandhurst 
2. USMA Gold
3. Company F1 @f1.firehouse 
4. University of North Georgia @ungcadets 
5. The College of St. Benedict St. John's University @fightingsaintsbattalion

Class of 2022 Cadet Elizabeth Bradley, Company I-3 @i3_icemen, set a new women’s record for the Indoor Obstacle Course Test Wednesday with an official time of 2:20. node.text:
Meet Cadet Anna Tovkach, Deputy Brigade Commander

Tovkach, an Environmental Engineering major, track athlete, and Chi Alpha Sigma scholar from Gainesville, Florida, chose West Point for a combination of reasons. She knew that a service academy would fit her personality and wanted to be far from home in a way that challenged her to be more independent. When she spoke with West Point cadets, they were brutally honest about the difficulty of training and daily life but emphasized the importance of the relationships they had easily formed here. After three years here, West Point has been challenging and uncomfortable most of the time, but she is proud of the person, athlete, friend, and scholar she has become. 

“I hope to set the example for every cadet by showing that your path here does not have to look like anyone else’s. I want to inspire people around me to be passionate about everything they do and have passion for the success of the people around them. I cannot emphasize enough the importance of the relationships we will form here. It is my goal to embody discipline in the little things, which can add up to greatness and unshakable character.” 

Photos by CDT Ellington Ward, Class of 2022, CMG CIC

@cadetmediagroup @dean.usma @westpointadmissions @goarmytrack @e.w.photo @commandant.usmilitaryacademy @anna.tovkach #WestPoint #USMA #leadership

"What a Crass Mass of Brass and Glass! What a Bold Mold of Rolled Gold. . . .! "

The United States Military Academy began the tradition of college rings in 1835, with the chosen motto, ""Amicitiae Periculique Foedus (Danger Brings Forth Friendship)" engraved on the ring. The small rings were designed to be worn on the pinky finger and had flat crests used to seal wax on letters. 

This year, #USMA2022's unique crest and motto, "For Many Stand the Few" will bond them forever and is a wonderful symbol of character, pride, and unity. #WestPoint #USMA #ClassRing @dean.usma @commandant.usmilitaryacademy @westpointadmissions @usma.dmi @cadetmediagroup 

For more photos of the Class of 2022 Ring Ceremony, please visit West Point Flickr

📸: Cadets Tyler Williams, Stephen Litterini, Kyle Swindler, Eli Wright, Josias Galindo

#MeetYour First Captain #USMA2022 CDT Holland Pratt

Pratt, a Military History major and Middle East Regional Studies minor from Liberty Lake, Washington, chose West Point to help others and be surrounded by people with a similar mission and mindset for service.

“I hope to empower cadets at West Point to feel they have the tools and opportunities to pursue excellence and influence those around them in a positive manner. West Point often pinpoints your weaknesses and makes you work at them, but if we stay focused on serving those around us and remember the legacy of servant leadership we have inherited as cadets and service members, we can overcome those difficulties and be better prepared to lead to the best of our abilities as platoon leaders and beyond. ‘Eager to Serve, Willing to Lead’ always!” 

@dean.usma @westpointadmissions @commandant.usmilitaryacademy @usma.dmi @westpoint_scholarshipprogram @cadetmediagroup
